Inline Styles

Embedded Styles

External Style Sheet

Inline Styles : 

  --> Styles are defined for every element using "style" attribute
  
  --> Pros : Faster in Rendering
  
  --> Cons : Lack of Re-usability
  
  Example : <div style="attribute.value"></div>
  
Embedded Style :

  --> Styles are defined by using <style> in head or body
  
  --> Pros : Re-usability
  
  --> Cons : Slower in Rendering
  
  Syntax : 
  
      <head>
          <style>
          </style>
      </head>
      
  FAQ : What is the difference between mentioning <style> in <head> and <style> in <body> ? 
  
  Ans : <style> in <head> : Styles gets loaded to Browser Memory First and then applied to elements
  
        <style> in <body> : Styles gets loaded and Applied to Elements Directly
        
  FAQ : Can we define styles in both Sections?
  
  Ans : Yes
  
  Note : You can keep <style> out of <html> . It is Un-official but it is faster in speed.
  
  FAQ: What is MIME type for Styles?
  
  Ans : text/css
  
    Syntax : <style type="text/css"> </style>
    
  FAQ : What is the media type for styles?
  
  Ans : screen,print,speech
  
  Note : You can't access embedded styles from another page
  
External Style Sheets [Cascading Style Sheets]

  --> Styles are maintained in a seperate StyleSheet
  
  --> Clean Seperation of markup and styles and Provides Re-usability across page
  
  --> External Stylesheet --> leads to more no.of.request for page
  
  --> More no.of.requests increases page load time will increase
  
  Steps
  
    1.Create a new Stylesheet
    
        effects.css
        h1{
          background-color:red;
          color:white;
          text-align:center;
        }
        
    2.Link Stylesheet to any page
    
      <link rel="stylesheet" href = "../src/styles/effects.css" type="text/css">
      
   FAQ : What is Minification?
   
   Ans : 1.It is a technique used to reduce file size
    
         2.It is not a Zip or RAR File
         
   Note : Minified css file --> only in Production [style.min.css]
      
          css file --> only in development [style.css]
         
    
